“Great leaders do not give excuses for failure. They find the reasons to succeed” -Anonymous The queues are long-winding and tortuous. The crowds of fuel-seekers are agitated and visibly angry. The attendants at the few fuel filling stations are ever-ready to attend mostly to the highest bidders, ready to part with some extra cash. Not long after, the jostling for the much-needed fuel degenerates into bloody fisticuffs, as verbal missiles are exchanged more freely than bullets at the battlefield. Valuable man-hours are wasted and lost, but who really cares. At least, not right here and now in Nigeria.  